  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection Monitoring for corrective response management</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR will use $500,000 from CERF to deploy protection monitors and apply monitoring procedures adapted to contexts considered under the anticipatory agenda to inform the planning and progress of the Anticipatory Action pilot through a protection lens. Short-term refresher trainings will be undertaken, so as to ensure that the protection monitors are able to take on their tasks. In addition, UNHCR will support at least 200 persons with a one-off cash disbursement of $50 to help them access emergency services and other specialized support services. In total, 38,000 people will be assisted by the project, including 9,497 women and 9,803 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
